Additionally, Matthew Sharp portrays [[Henry Guyrich (Earth-10005)|Henry Guyrich]]. Rhona Shekter and Kenneth McGregor appear as Erik's [[Edie Lehnsherr (Earth-10005)|mother]] and [[Jakob Lehnsherr (Earth-10005)|father]], respectively. {{WP|Shawn Roberts}} portrays [[David (Rogue's Boyfriend) (Earth-10005)|David]], Rogue's boyfriend. Donna Goodhand and John E. Nelles appear as Rogue's [[Priscilla D'Ancanto (Earth-10005)|mother]] and [[Owen D'Ancanto (Earth-10005)|father]], respectively. Kevin Rushton portrays cage fighter Stu. {{WP|Sumela Kay}}, {{WP|Shawn Ashmore}}, Katrina Florece, Alex Burton appear as [[Xavier's School for Gifted Youngsters]] students [[Katherine Pryde (Earth-10005)|Kitty Pryde]], [[Robert Drake (Earth-10005)|Bobby Drake]], [[Jubilation Lee (Earth-10005)|Jubilee]], and [[John Allerdyce (Earth-10005)|John Allerdyce]], respectively. {{WP|Matt Weinberg}} portrays Tommy, a boy at the beach. [[Stan Lee]] cameos as a hot dog vendor, while writers [[Tom DeSanto]] and [[David Hayter]] cameo as cops. Amy Leland provides the voice of [[Cerebro (Mutant Detector)|Cerebro]]. David Black portrays the President of the United States.

